 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-13408497 Portugal's 78bn euro bail-out is formally approved] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-13408497 |date=20110518135513 }} BBC News Business, 16 May 2011, Retrieved 19 May 2011</ref>

儘管只有少數歐元區國家的主權債務錄得顯著增長，但問題卻困擾著整個歐元區。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/0,1518,769329,00.html |title="How the Euro Became Europe's Greatest Threat," Der Spiegel, 20 June 2011. |accessdate=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2012-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308032003/http://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/0,1518,769329,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2011年5月，債務危機因為希臘再度在支付到期公債方面出現問題而重新湧現。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2011/jun/19/greek-debt-crisis-eurozone-ministers?intcmp=239 |title="Greek debt crisis: eurozone ministers meet amid deepening gloom," The Guardian, 19 June 2011. |accessdate=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2012-09-05 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ARjiJZ90?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2011/jun/19/greek-debt-crisis-eurozone-ministers?intcmp=239 |dead-url=no }}</ref>不少希臘國民因反對該國政府計劃推出的緊縮開支措施而發起上街示威，群情激憤。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.economist.com/blogs/newsbook/2011/06/greeces-political-crisis |title="A long day in Greece," The Economist, 16 June 2011 |access-date=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025453/http://www.economist.com/blogs/newsbook/2011/06/greeces-political-crisis |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jun/19/athens-protests-syntagma-austerity-protests |title="Athens protests: Syntagma Square on frontline of European austerity protests," The Guardian, 19 June 2011. |access-date=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2013-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611060238/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2011/jun/19/athens-protests-syntagma-austerity-protests |dead-url=no }}</ref>一直到2011年6月底，希臘政府勉強通過新一輪的緊縮開支方案，進而獲得歐盟領袖承諾提供援助支持希臘經濟，該國引發的危機才得以受到控制。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13886099 |title="EU leaders pledge to do what is needed to help Greece". BBC, 23 June 2011 |accessdate=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2013-07-19 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6IEpYpvF1?url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-13886099 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==相關評論==
[[File:George_Papandreou_and_Jose_Manuel_Barroso.jpg|thumb]]和歐盟委員會主席[[若澤·曼努埃爾·巴羅佐|若澤·曼努埃爾·巴羅佐]]商討2011年債務問題]]
歐債危機是歐元區自1999年設立以來的首場危機，危機也引起不少輿論對歐元區的質疑，正如英國《[[金融時報|金融時報]]》專欄作家[[塞繆爾·布理坦|塞繆爾·布理坦爵士]]（Sir Samuel Brittan）引用希臘基金經理[[賈森·馬諾洛普洛斯|賈森·馬諾洛普洛斯]]（Jason Manolopoulos）的說法，<ref>{{cite web| title = Who is winning in the race for recovery | author=Samuel Brittan|  work=Financial Times | accessdate =12 May 2011|url = http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/e4379f48-7cc5-11e0-994d-00144feabdc0.html}}</ref>認為「結果顯示歐元區與[[最優貨幣區|最優貨幣區]]差距甚遠」；<ref>{{cite book| title=Greece's 'Odious' Debt: The Looting of the Hellenic Republic by the Euro, the Political Elite and the Investment Community.| author=Manolopoulos, J| url=http://greecesodiousdebt.anthempressblog.com/| location=London, May 2011| publisher=Anthem Press| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110817115807/http://greecesodiousdebt.anthempressblog.com/| archivedate=2011-08-17}}</ref>另一英國經濟學者[[尼埃爾·費格遜|尼埃爾·費格遜]]（Niall Ferguson）在2010年的時候也評論到，「正在浮現的主權債務危機……是西方世界的財政危機」。<ref>{{cite web | title = A Greek crisis is coming to America | author = Niall Ferguson | work = Financial Times | date = 10 February 2010 | accessdate = 18 April 2011 | url = http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/f90bca10-1679-11df-bf44-00144feab49a.html | archive-date = 2011-05-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110501134456/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/f90bca10-1679-11df-bf44-00144feab49a.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>不過，《金融時報》在2011年5月的另一篇評論文章則指出，美元面臨的處境可能比歐元還要危險。<ref>Merk, Axel (2011) [http://www.google.com/search?q=site:ft.com+%22dollar+in+graver+danger+than+the+euro%22 Dollar in graver danger than the euro] {{Wayback|url=http://www.google.com/search?q=site:ft.com+%22dollar+in+graver+danger+than+the+euro%22 |date=20160131093341 }} The Financial Times, 11 May 2011, Retrieved 19 May 2011</ref>

2013年5月，位於德國柏林的「{{link-de|德國經濟研究所|Deutsches Institut für Wirtschaftsforschung Berlin}}」（{{lang-de|DIW Berlin}}）的景氣研究小組主任接受德國{{link-de|商業報|Handelsblatt}}訪問時指出，依據該小組的研究結論，貪腐、綁樁政治、缺乏彈性的勞動市場－－這些才是歐債危機國家們的問題根源。它們阻礙了新經濟力道的抬頭，振興景氣方案救不了這些沉疴。<ref>{{cite news|title=DIW-Experte: Konjunkturprogramme helfen Krisenländern nicht|url=http://www.handelsblatt.com/politik/konjunktur/nachrichten/diw-experte-konjunkturprogramme-helfen-krisenlaendern-nicht/8177942.html?utm_source=twitterfeed&utm_medium=twitter|work=Handelblatt|date=2013-05-08|accessdate=2013-05-08|archive-date=2016-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816143024/http://www.handelsblatt.com/politik/konjunktur/nachrichten/diw-experte-konjunkturprogramme-helfen-krisenlaendern-nicht/8177942.html?utm_source=twitterfeed&utm_medium=twitter|dead-url=no}}</ref>

